  "abstract": "Gingelly (Sesamum indicum L.)is one of the important oilseed. Crops grown in northern Karnataka. The Crop suffers from number of Foliar Diseases of which powdery mildew(Oidium sp.) affects at flowering stage and onwards and causes considerable loss of yield………………………",
